# 27. Write a Query using CASE WHEN

### Answer

CASE works like an IF-ELSE statement.

```sql
SELECT Name,
Salary,
CASE
WHEN Salary > 80000 THEN 'High Salary'
WHEN Salary BETWEEN 50000 AND 80000 THEN 'Medium Salary'
ELSE 'Low Salary'
END AS SalaryCategory
FROM Employees;
```

### Uses

* Data classification
* Conditional calculations
* Replacing IF-ELSE logic

