# 29. Explain ACID Properties

### Answer

ACID ensures database transactions are reliable.

### A — Atomicity

A transaction is completed entirely or not at all.

Example

If money is transferred from Account A to Account B, both operations must succeed or both must fail.

---

### C — Consistency

The database remains valid before and after the transaction.

---

### I — Isolation

Multiple transactions should not interfere with one another.

---

### D — Durability

Once a transaction is committed, the changes are permanent even if the system crashes.

### Interview Tip

Almost every SQL interview asks about ACID properties.

